## Extending the System

### Add a new rule (root-cause pattern)

Edit `src/network_rca/agents/rca_agent.py` and append a `_Rule` instance
to the `_RULES` list:

```python
_Rule(
    category="bgp_flap",
    title="BGP Session Instability",
    description="...",
    required={MetricType.ERROR_RATE},
    optional={MetricType.CPU_UTILIZATION},
    base_confidence=0.60,
    actions=["Check BGP peer state", "..."],
),
```

### Add a new metric type

1. Add the enum value to `MetricType` in `src/network_rca/models/network_event.py`.
2. Add its unit and absolute threshold to `_METRIC_UNITS` / `_ABSOLUTE_UPPER` /
   `_ABSOLUTE_LOWER` in the ingestion and detection agents.

### Plug in an LLM

The `BaseAgent.run()` contract is intentionally simple: every agent
receives and returns a plain `dict` context.  To add LLM-powered reasoning:

1. Subclass `BaseAgent` (e.g. `LLMRCAAgent`).
2. Serialise the anomalies from context and call your preferred LLM API.
3. Inject the agent into `RCAOrchestrator._agents` in place of `RCAAgent`.

